WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.490 --> 00:00:24.770
(Transcribed by TurboScribe.ai. Go Unlimited to remove this message.) ACT III.

2
00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:25.830
SCENE I.

3
00:00:26.450 --> 00:00:27.890
A SALOON FURNISHED.

4
00:00:28.190 --> 00:00:31.049
WINDOWS AND BALCONY CENTRE, DOORS RIGHT AND

5
00:00:31.049 --> 00:00:31.530
LEFT.

6
00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:34.270
A MADONNA RIGHT, CHAIR LEFT.

7
00:00:34.850 --> 00:00:37.130
BLAZARILLO DISCOVERED, ARRANGING TABLE

8
00:00:37.130 --> 00:00:37.510
RIGHT.

9
00:00:38.010 --> 00:00:39.750
I was prepared for the arrival of Don

10
00:00:39.750 --> 00:00:40.070
José.

11
00:00:41.330 --> 00:00:43.250
What can be the meaning of these mysterious

12
00:00:43.250 --> 00:00:43.810
proceedings?

13
00:00:44.850 --> 00:00:48.030
This house so suddenly engaged, this lady

14
00:00:48.030 --> 00:00:50.030
for whom he seems to entertain so great

15
00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:50.810
a respect?

16
00:00:51.830 --> 00:00:53.070
Should the queen hear of this?

17
00:00:53.790 --> 00:00:55.750
Farewell to the Count's hopes of conquest.

18
00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:58.070
Ah, he is here.

19
00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:01.610
Enter DON JOSÉ, LEFT A SECOND ENTRANCE.

20
00:01:02.050 --> 00:01:03.430
Has anyone arrived?

21
00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:05.650
Yes, my lord, the lady.

22
00:01:06.130 --> 00:01:07.710
She is now in that chamber.

23
00:01:08.150 --> 00:01:09.310
The servants and horses?

24
00:01:09.810 --> 00:01:11.110
Returned instantly to Madrid.

25
00:01:12.090 --> 00:01:13.470
Shall I announce your lordship?

26
00:01:13.730 --> 00:01:14.150
No.

27
00:01:14.370 --> 00:01:16.390
Do you remember the cavalier who addressed

28
00:01:16.390 --> 00:01:18.490
me yesterday near the escuril?

29
00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:19.650
Yes, my lord.

30
00:01:19.930 --> 00:01:20.990
Was it not the king?

31
00:01:21.650 --> 00:01:22.190
Silence.

32
00:01:22.510 --> 00:01:23.790
Passes him to left.

33
00:01:24.170 --> 00:01:25.410
He will be here to-night.

34
00:01:25.930 --> 00:01:28.610
He alone must be admitted to this apartment.

35
00:01:29.030 --> 00:01:30.890
Should any others present themselves, my

36
00:01:30.890 --> 00:01:31.230
lord?

37
00:01:31.650 --> 00:01:33.090
Refuse them admittance.

38
00:01:33.690 --> 00:01:36.330
If they insist, you have your arquebus.

39
00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:37.210
Use it.

40
00:01:37.590 --> 00:01:38.730
I will use it, my lord.

41
00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:39.330
Go.

42
00:01:39.670 --> 00:01:42.230
Blazarillo exit left's second entrance.

43
00:01:42.650 --> 00:01:46.170
This Don César, who I thought dead, how

44
00:01:46.170 --> 00:01:47.190
did he escape?

45
00:01:47.810 --> 00:01:50.550
His presence at this moment would ruin all.

46
00:01:51.210 --> 00:01:52.790
I will delay no longer.

47
00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:55.810
Tonight shall see my plans accomplished.

48
00:01:56.470 --> 00:01:59.210
The king will be here anon, and I

49
00:01:59.210 --> 00:02:01.550
have already dispatched a message to the

50
00:02:01.550 --> 00:02:04.230
queen, apprising her of her husband's

51
00:02:04.230 --> 00:02:04.790
infidelity.

52
00:02:05.590 --> 00:02:07.550
She comes to-night to the neighbouring

53
00:02:07.550 --> 00:02:08.650
palace of Aránguez.

54
00:02:09.289 --> 00:02:11.890
There will I seek her and urge a

55
00:02:11.890 --> 00:02:15.310
suit, which, in revenge, she may accord me.

56
00:02:15.650 --> 00:02:17.190
A horn at a distance.

57
00:02:17.750 --> 00:02:19.870
Ah, the signal of the king.

58
00:02:20.370 --> 00:02:23.410
Enter Maritana, right second entrance.

59
00:02:23.830 --> 00:02:25.290
What means that?

60
00:02:25.810 --> 00:02:26.930
Seize Don José.

61
00:02:27.550 --> 00:02:29.810
Ah, the Count de Santarém.

62
00:02:30.030 --> 00:02:32.030
Don José with a ceremony.

63
00:02:32.630 --> 00:02:35.550
I trust that my orders have been punctually

64
00:02:35.550 --> 00:02:36.630
obeyed, madame?

65
00:02:37.270 --> 00:02:39.090
There is nothing you require?

66
00:02:39.690 --> 00:02:41.730
Nothing, nothing, I thank you.

67
00:02:41.730 --> 00:02:44.970
Then your bright dreams are realised.

68
00:02:45.630 --> 00:02:48.710
You have title, splendour, homage.

69
00:02:49.370 --> 00:02:51.850
Did I not prophesy rightly, madame?

70
00:02:52.550 --> 00:02:54.110
I have kept every promise.

71
00:02:54.490 --> 00:02:58.110
You have, Don José, though the Countess de

72
00:02:58.110 --> 00:03:01.570
Bassan already regressed the wishes of

73
00:03:01.570 --> 00:03:02.510
Maritana.

74
00:03:03.170 --> 00:03:03.890
Weeps.

75
00:03:04.390 --> 00:03:04.970
Wherefore?

76
00:03:05.490 --> 00:03:06.710
Why these tears?

77
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:10.050
I think me not ungrateful to you and

78
00:03:10.050 --> 00:03:13.050
the queen, but amidst the splendour which

79
00:03:13.050 --> 00:03:15.870
surrounds me I often sigh for the free

80
00:03:15.870 --> 00:03:18.690
course and happy thoughts of the poor

81
00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:19.970
dancing girl.

82
00:03:20.270 --> 00:03:20.810
Hush.

83
00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:23.850
Enter Lazarillo, left second entrance.

84
00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:25.250
He is here, my lord.

85
00:03:25.430 --> 00:03:25.990
Who?

86
00:03:26.530 --> 00:03:28.410
Your husband, madame.

87
00:03:28.810 --> 00:03:29.710
My husband?

88
00:03:31.510 --> 00:03:32.270
Weeps.

89
00:03:33.150 --> 00:03:35.810
The king enters, left second entrance.

90
00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:39.390
Don José salutes him respectfully, and signs

91
00:03:39.390 --> 00:03:42.150
to Lazarillo and both exsuant right.

92
00:03:43.210 --> 00:03:44.210
King aside.

93
00:03:44.810 --> 00:03:46.610
At length we are together.

94
00:03:47.190 --> 00:03:47.870
Allowed.

95
00:03:48.170 --> 00:03:48.770
Maritana.

96
00:03:49.510 --> 00:03:51.010
Maritana aside.

97
00:03:51.450 --> 00:03:55.050
Evan, how I tremble even at his voice.

98
00:03:55.430 --> 00:03:56.830
Why did you not answer me?

99
00:03:57.470 --> 00:03:59.370
Why did you not approach me?

100
00:04:00.170 --> 00:04:03.570
Pardon me, my lord, but— Your lips are

101
00:04:03.570 --> 00:04:04.510
colourless.

102
00:04:05.170 --> 00:04:06.510
Takes her hand.

103
00:04:06.810 --> 00:04:10.290
Your hand is icy as death.

104
00:04:10.830 --> 00:04:13.170
Maritana taking away her hand.

105
00:04:13.630 --> 00:04:15.130
I— Aside.

106
00:04:15.690 --> 00:04:17.170
I cannot speak.

107
00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:20.010
Wherefore this chilling welcome?

108
00:04:20.630 --> 00:04:21.770
Are you not happy?

109
00:04:22.510 --> 00:04:23.770
Maritana aside.

110
00:04:24.170 --> 00:04:25.090
Happy?

111
00:04:25.510 --> 00:04:26.070
Allowed.

112
00:04:26.390 --> 00:04:27.990
How shall I answer you?

113
00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:31.010
Can you wonder at my uneasiness?

114
00:04:31.570 --> 00:04:34.090
Our strange marriage, the distance which

115
00:04:34.090 --> 00:04:36.670
separates us, the noble and the beggar.

116
00:04:36.970 --> 00:04:39.830
I still feel how much you are my

117
00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:40.470
superior.

118
00:04:41.190 --> 00:04:43.730
I dare not raise my eyes to yours.

119
00:04:43.970 --> 00:04:46.530
I— I fear you.

120
00:04:47.170 --> 00:04:48.250
Fear me?

121
00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:50.050
With what fear?

122
00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:51.890
We would know.

123
00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:52.830
Pauses.

124
00:04:52.830 --> 00:04:57.350
Oh, Maritana, how you wrong me by such

125
00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:58.090
feelings.

126
00:04:58.890 --> 00:05:02.890
I love you, and would sacrifice all to

127
00:05:02.890 --> 00:05:05.110
know my love returned.

128
00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:08.650
Kisses her hand, which she withdraws.

129
00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:09.830
What?

130
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:14.230
Don José told me you waited my company

131
00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:15.550
with impatience.

132
00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:17.770
He has deceived me.

133
00:05:18.200 --> 00:05:20.350
Not you alone, my lord.

134
00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:23.550
I also have been deceived.

135
00:05:24.130 --> 00:05:24.510
How?

136
00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:26.770
By this union.

137
00:05:27.650 --> 00:05:29.970
The husband that he assigned me was one

138
00:05:29.970 --> 00:05:34.550
proscribed and ruined, but still both brave

139
00:05:34.550 --> 00:05:35.450
and noble.

140
00:05:36.030 --> 00:05:38.470
His sword was ever the defender of the

141
00:05:38.470 --> 00:05:41.410
weak, his voice the advocate of the

142
00:05:41.410 --> 00:05:41.970
oppressed.

143
00:05:42.690 --> 00:05:45.770
Where'er he went, mirth followed after.

144
00:05:46.350 --> 00:05:49.890
A wanderer like myself, I felt almost as

145
00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:50.430
equal.

146
00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:53.270
I thought that he would know my heart,

147
00:05:53.390 --> 00:05:55.470
and from his memory of the past, forgive

148
00:05:55.470 --> 00:05:56.770
errors of the present.

149
00:05:57.510 --> 00:05:59.030
Nor shall you be deceived.

150
00:05:59.970 --> 00:06:03.330
Each luxury shall minister to your desires.

151
00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:07.510
My love shall be so prodigal that, in

152
00:06:07.510 --> 00:06:11.550
spite of all, you shall return my passion.

153
00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:16.330
Embracing her, Maritana disengaging herself.

154
00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:19.870
Unhand me, count, unhand me.

155
00:06:20.250 --> 00:06:21.430
Keen and raged.

156
00:06:21.990 --> 00:06:23.210
I understand.

157
00:06:24.150 --> 00:06:25.670
You love another, Maritana.

158
00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:29.610
Your heart, I thought, never beat with

159
00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:31.490
passion or desire.

160
00:06:32.370 --> 00:06:34.550
I am deceived.

161
00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:37.730
For this I've made you what you are.

162
00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:41.150
Ingrate, to your chamber, madam.

163
00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:44.910
You must learn the duty you owe your

164
00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:47.030
lord and husband.

165
00:06:47.910 --> 00:06:49.150
I obey you.

166
00:06:49.430 --> 00:06:51.310
You have reason for your anger.

167
00:06:51.710 --> 00:06:54.210
I obey you, my lord and my master.

168
00:06:54.790 --> 00:06:56.190
Exit right door.

169
00:06:56.590 --> 00:06:57.930
Doth she relent?

170
00:06:58.690 --> 00:06:59.930
Why should I hesitate?

171
00:07:00.870 --> 00:07:02.730
Going towards right door.

172
00:07:03.210 --> 00:07:05.390
She may yet be won.

173
00:07:05.390 --> 00:07:06.710
A shot heard.

174
00:07:07.570 --> 00:07:10.550
Don Cesar enters over balcony, left centre.

175
00:07:10.710 --> 00:07:13.090
That's a villainous way to receive a guest.

176
00:07:13.510 --> 00:07:15.350
What the devil have I done to be

177
00:07:15.350 --> 00:07:17.190
continually made a target?

178
00:07:17.630 --> 00:07:19.770
The king retires and observes.

179
00:07:20.850 --> 00:07:23.790
Lazario enters left centre with an arquebus

180
00:07:23.790 --> 00:07:24.650
in his hand.

181
00:07:25.670 --> 00:07:26.870
Lazario starts.

182
00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:29.470
Don Cesar.

183
00:07:30.090 --> 00:07:31.170
Exit left door.

184
00:07:31.370 --> 00:07:31.710
Well?

185
00:07:32.110 --> 00:07:33.190
Seize the king.

186
00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:34.290
Pardon, señor.

187
00:07:35.050 --> 00:07:37.410
I had not the honour of seeing you

188
00:07:37.410 --> 00:07:38.650
till this moment.

189
00:07:38.970 --> 00:07:39.890
King bows.

190
00:07:40.630 --> 00:07:43.130
Why did you enter by that window?

191
00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:46.830
Well, señor, simply because the door was

192
00:07:46.830 --> 00:07:47.230
shut.

193
00:07:47.690 --> 00:07:50.130
I am in no humour for jesting.

194
00:07:50.790 --> 00:07:51.830
What is your motive?

195
00:07:52.530 --> 00:07:53.490
A pardonable one.

196
00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:56.250
By the light of the moon, I saw

197
00:07:56.250 --> 00:07:59.130
in the next balcony a very pretty woman,

198
00:07:59.630 --> 00:08:01.350
and I wished to speak to her.

199
00:08:01.670 --> 00:08:02.530
What, sir?

200
00:08:02.530 --> 00:08:04.430
I knocked at the door.

201
00:08:05.090 --> 00:08:06.770
The porter refused me admittance.

202
00:08:07.070 --> 00:08:09.110
How was I to get in?

203
00:08:09.610 --> 00:08:11.710
There was but one opening, and that was

204
00:08:11.710 --> 00:08:12.190
the window.

205
00:08:12.830 --> 00:08:15.510
I was about to ascend when whizz came

206
00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:16.810
a bullet through my hat.

207
00:08:17.270 --> 00:08:18.950
Shell's hole in his hat.

208
00:08:19.150 --> 00:08:20.450
Sacred hospitality.

209
00:08:21.110 --> 00:08:22.710
How you are insulted.

210
00:08:23.110 --> 00:08:25.210
What is your business with this lady?

211
00:08:25.790 --> 00:08:26.330
Pardon me.

212
00:08:26.850 --> 00:08:28.790
I never violate confidence.

213
00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:30.890
I merely wish to see her.

214
00:08:31.110 --> 00:08:31.590
That's all.

215
00:08:31.590 --> 00:08:32.429
Impertinent.

216
00:08:32.970 --> 00:08:35.710
I desire you to quit the room.

217
00:08:36.169 --> 00:08:38.169
After the trouble I've had to get here?

218
00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:42.190
Are you— The master of this house.

219
00:08:42.750 --> 00:08:44.090
The master of this house?

220
00:08:44.370 --> 00:08:44.830
Hmm.

221
00:08:45.270 --> 00:08:45.970
This house.

222
00:08:46.810 --> 00:08:49.570
Where have I seen the Countess de Bazin?

223
00:08:49.950 --> 00:08:51.610
You know her, then?

224
00:08:52.070 --> 00:08:52.770
Very slightly.

225
00:08:53.290 --> 00:08:55.950
I've only seen her for about ten minutes,

226
00:08:56.210 --> 00:08:59.110
but if she resides here, may I ask

227
00:08:59.110 --> 00:08:59.950
your name?

228
00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:01.870
King Hotterly.

229
00:09:02.510 --> 00:09:04.930
I am— Pauses.

230
00:09:05.330 --> 00:09:07.670
Looks at the door of Maritana's chamber.

231
00:09:08.350 --> 00:09:12.910
I am Don Cesar de Bazin.

232
00:09:13.790 --> 00:09:14.630
Sits.

233
00:09:15.050 --> 00:09:15.290
Eh?

234
00:09:16.110 --> 00:09:17.690
Don Cesar de Bazin?

235
00:09:18.010 --> 00:09:18.710
Aside.

236
00:09:19.230 --> 00:09:20.030
Eghad.

237
00:09:20.270 --> 00:09:23.630
I excel a phoenix, for two Don Cesars

238
00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:25.950
have arisen from my ashes.

239
00:09:26.230 --> 00:09:27.810
Enter Lazzarillo Centre.

240
00:09:27.810 --> 00:09:32.410
Now that I have satisfied you, I demand

241
00:09:32.410 --> 00:09:34.330
to know your name.

242
00:09:34.650 --> 00:09:35.930
Don Cesar aside.

243
00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:38.450
The unblushing rascal.

244
00:09:38.950 --> 00:09:41.450
Lazzarillo whispers aside to Don Cesar.

245
00:09:41.870 --> 00:09:42.790
It is the king.

246
00:09:43.330 --> 00:09:44.470
Exit the left door.

247
00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:45.870
Eh, Larissio?

248
00:09:46.170 --> 00:09:47.450
You hesitate, sir.

249
00:09:48.050 --> 00:09:49.350
Don Cesar aside.

250
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:50.650
The king here?

251
00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:53.510
I understand all.

252
00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:55.950
My question embarrasses you.

253
00:09:56.430 --> 00:09:57.970
I demand an answer.

254
00:09:58.430 --> 00:09:58.730
Certainly.

255
00:09:59.270 --> 00:10:02.110
If you are Don Cesar de Bazin— Seats

256
00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:04.910
himself left centre with dignity, and places

257
00:10:04.910 --> 00:10:06.390
his hat on his head.

258
00:10:06.870 --> 00:10:08.810
I am the king of Spain.

259
00:10:09.290 --> 00:10:09.890
What?

260
00:10:10.490 --> 00:10:11.470
The king?

261
00:10:11.870 --> 00:10:14.870
The king of Spain.

262
00:10:15.350 --> 00:10:15.950
You?

263
00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:19.790
Don Cesar, tauntingly and pleasantly.

264
00:10:19.790 --> 00:10:22.590
As surely as you are Don Cesar de

265
00:10:22.590 --> 00:10:23.170
Bazin.

266
00:10:23.970 --> 00:10:27.510
Ah, it astonishes you to see Majesty

267
00:10:27.510 --> 00:10:29.810
unattended at this hour of the night, at

268
00:10:29.810 --> 00:10:32.370
the door of a pretty woman who is

269
00:10:32.370 --> 00:10:33.090
not the queen?

270
00:10:33.890 --> 00:10:36.150
There's nothing surprising in it, I assure

271
00:10:36.150 --> 00:10:36.410
you.

272
00:10:36.890 --> 00:10:38.410
I was out of spirits.

273
00:10:39.130 --> 00:10:42.670
Kings require relaxation sometimes, but not

274
00:10:42.670 --> 00:10:44.270
a word of this royal folly.

275
00:10:45.310 --> 00:10:47.670
Though with you, Don Cesar, I may rest

276
00:10:47.670 --> 00:10:48.430
satisfied.

277
00:10:48.430 --> 00:10:51.130
You will not betray our secret.

278
00:10:51.570 --> 00:10:52.630
King aside.

279
00:10:53.690 --> 00:10:54.310
Insolent.

280
00:10:55.070 --> 00:10:56.670
Who can he be?

281
00:10:57.350 --> 00:10:58.510
Ha, by the by.

282
00:10:58.790 --> 00:11:00.470
I remember Don Cesar.

283
00:11:01.070 --> 00:11:02.670
I know all my subjects.

284
00:11:03.030 --> 00:11:06.330
A witty, gallant fellow, somewhat of my own

285
00:11:06.330 --> 00:11:06.710
humour.

286
00:11:07.170 --> 00:11:09.270
He killed the captain of our guard in

287
00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:12.030
