680
00:25:24.530 --> 00:25:26.230
Yet you cannot leave this room.

681
00:25:26.650 --> 00:25:29.070
The king puts his hands to his face

682
00:25:29.070 --> 00:25:30.990
and falls in a chair.

683
00:25:31.410 --> 00:25:34.150
Every moment is an age of agony, and

684
00:25:34.150 --> 00:25:36.150
yet you cannot quit this place to satisfy

685
00:25:36.150 --> 00:25:36.750
your doubt.

686
00:25:37.390 --> 00:25:39.510
All that you made me suffer you are

687
00:25:39.510 --> 00:25:42.710
now enduring, and yet you cannot stir but

688
00:25:42.710 --> 00:25:43.770
at my will.

689
00:25:43.990 --> 00:25:45.650
King points to door.

690
00:25:45.650 --> 00:25:49.650
Don César, at your peril, hesitate a moment

691
00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:50.270
longer.

692
00:25:50.910 --> 00:25:53.230
This retribution is terrible, is it not?

693
00:25:53.530 --> 00:25:54.590
Take up your sword.

694
00:25:55.250 --> 00:25:55.690
Rises.

695
00:25:56.410 --> 00:25:58.110
I am a king no longer.

696
00:25:58.810 --> 00:26:01.550
Your treason forces me to become your equal.

697
00:26:02.330 --> 00:26:05.590
Defend yourself and save me from becoming an

698
00:26:05.590 --> 00:26:06.130
assassin.

699
00:26:06.770 --> 00:26:09.730
Maritana crosses centre and is put back by

700
00:26:09.730 --> 00:26:10.610
Don César.

701
00:26:10.950 --> 00:26:13.270
Oh, sire, for heaven's sake!

702
00:26:13.850 --> 00:26:14.610
King left.

703
00:26:15.250 --> 00:26:18.710
Take up your sword or I will strike.

704
00:26:19.030 --> 00:26:20.590
You will be too late.

705
00:26:20.870 --> 00:26:21.470
Too late?

706
00:26:21.930 --> 00:26:22.450
How?

707
00:26:22.770 --> 00:26:25.090
When did a Spanish gentleman hesitate to

708
00:26:25.090 --> 00:26:27.050
revenge an insult to his king?

709
00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:30.050
